("Slide 2: Why Do We Need Django?",
 "Traditional web development involves repetitive coding and manual configuration. "
 "Handling security manually increases the risk of vulnerabilities. "
 "Django provides built-in tools and a structured architecture for rapid and secure development."),

("Slide 3: What is Django?",
 "Django is an open-source Python web framework that follows the batteries-included philosophy. "
 "It allows developers to focus on application logic instead of basic setup tasks."),

("Slide 4: Django Architecture (MVT)",
 "Django follows the Model-View-Template architecture. "
 "The Model handles database logic, the View processes business logic, "
 "and the Template manages the user interface. "
 "This separation improves maintainability."),

("Slide 5: Key Features of Django",
 "Django supports rapid development, reusable components, "
 "a built-in admin interface, ORM, and strong security features by default."),

("Slide 6: Django ORM",
 "The Django ORM allows interaction with databases using Python objects instead of SQL queries. "
 "It supports multiple databases and improves code readability and maintainability."),

("Slide 7: Security in Django",
 "Django provides built-in protection against SQL injection and CSRF attacks. "
 "It includes secure authentication and automatic HTML escaping."),

("Slide 8: Real-World Applications of Django",
 "Django is used in content management systems, e-commerce platforms, "
 "social networking sites, and APIs. "
 "Companies like Instagram, Mozilla, and Pinterest use Django."),

("Slide 9: Advantages and Limitations",
 "Advantages include fast development, high security, and strong community support. "
 "Limitations include being heavy for small projects and less flexible for custom architectures."),

("Slide 10: Django vs Other Web Frameworks",
 "Django is a full-featured framework focused on structure and security. "
 "Flask is lightweight and flexible, while Express.js is JavaScript-based."),

("Slide 11: Conclusion & Future Scope",
 "Django simplifies backend development while ensuring scalability and security. "
 "It supports REST APIs and asynchronous features, making it future-ready.")
]

for title, note in speaker_notes:
pdf.add_page()
pdf.set_font("Arial", "B", 16)
pdf.multi_cell(0, 10, title)
pdf.ln(5)
pdf.set_font("Arial", size=12)
pdf.multi_cell(0, 8, note)

pdf.output("Django_Speaker_Notes.pdf")
